.TH INQ "1" "March 2026" "inq 0.1.2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
inq \- test repository management tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B inq
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] \fI\,<COMMAND>\/\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B inq
is a test repository management tool for tracking and analyzing test results.
It stores test run data in a local repository and provides commands for
running tests, viewing results, analyzing failures, and identifying slow or
flaky tests.
.PP
Configuration is read from
.B inquest.toml
(preferred) or
.B .testr.conf
(legacy INI format).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-C\fR, \fB\-\-directory\fR \fI\,DIRECTORY\/\fR
Repository path (defaults to current directory)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.SH COMMANDS
.SS "auto"
Auto\-detect project type and generate
.B inquest.toml
configuration file.
.PP
Detects the project type based on files present in the directory. Supported
project types include Cargo (Rust), pytest (Python), unittest/subunit
(Python), and prove (Perl).
.SS "init"
Initialize a new test repository.
.PP
Creates a
.B .inquest
directory with the necessary structure to store test results and metadata.
If a legacy
.B .testrepository/
directory exists, it will suggest running
.B inq upgrade
to convert to the new format.
.SS "run"
Run tests and load results.
.PP
Executes the test command from the configuration file and loads the results
into the repository. Displays a progress bar with color\-coded failure rates
and ETA based on historical test times.
.TP
\fB\-\-failing\fR
Run only the tests that failed in the last run
.TP
\fB\-\-force\-init\fR
Create repository if it doesn't exist
.TP
\fB\-\-auto\fR
Auto\-detect project type and generate inquest.toml if missing
.TP
\fB\-\-partial\fR
Partial run mode (update failing tests additively without clearing previous failures)
.TP
\fB\-\-load\-list\fR \fI\,FILE\/\fR
Only run tests listed in the named file (one test ID per line)
.TP
\fB\-j\fR, \fB\-\-parallel\fR [\fI\,N\/\fR]
Run tests in parallel across multiple workers (defaults to number of CPUs)
.TP
\fB\-\-concurrency\fR
Alias for \fB\-\-parallel\fR
.TP
\fB\-\-until\-failure\fR
Run tests repeatedly until they fail
.TP
\fB\-\-isolated\fR
Run each test in a separate process
.TP
\fB\-\-subunit\fR
Show output as a subunit stream
.TP
\fB\-\-all\-output\fR
Show output from all tests (by default only failed tests show output)
.TP
\fI\,TESTFILTER\/\fR ...
Test ID filters (regex patterns to filter which tests to run)
.PP
Additional arguments can be passed to the underlying test command after \fB\-\-\fR.
.PP
Exit code is 0 if all tests passed, 1 if there are failures.
.SS "load"
Load test results from stdin.
.PP
Reads test results from stdin in subunit format and stores them in the
repository.
.TP
\fB\-\-force\-init\fR
Create repository if it doesn't exist
.TP
\fB\-\-partial\fR
Partial run mode (update failing tests additively)
.SS "last"
Show results from a test run.
.PP
Displays test statistics and details about failed tests from a specific run
or the most recent run.
.TP
\fB\-r\fR, \fB\-\-run\fR \fI\,RUN_ID\/\fR
Run ID to show (defaults to latest; supports negative indices like \-1, \-2)
.TP
\fB\-\-subunit\fR
Show output as a subunit stream
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-output\fR
Don't show test output/tracebacks for failed tests
.PP
Exit code is 0 if all tests passed, 1 if there are failures.
.SS "failing"
Show failing tests from the last run.
.TP
\fB\-\-list\fR
List test IDs only, one per line (for scripting)
.TP
\fB\-\-subunit\fR
Show output as a subunit stream
.PP
Exit code is 0 if no failing tests, 1 if there are failures.
.SS "config"
Print the resolved effective configuration.
.PP
Shows the configuration that
.B inq run
would use, combining values from the config file
.RB ( inquest.toml ", " .inquest.toml ", or " .testr.conf ),
CLI overrides, and built\-in defaults. Each resolved value is annotated with its
source ([config], [cli], or [default]). Useful for debugging configuration
precedence.
.TP
\fB\-\-test\-timeout\fR \fI\,TIMEOUT\/\fR
Per\-test timeout override
.TP
\fB\-\-max\-duration\fR \fI\,DURATION\/\fR
Overall run\-duration override
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-output\-timeout\fR \fI\,DURATION\/\fR
No\-output timeout override
.TP
\fB\-\-order\fR \fI\,ORDER\/\fR
Test ordering strategy override
.TP
\fB\-j\fR, \fB\-\-parallel\fR \fI\,N\/\fR
Concurrency override
.SS "stats"
Show repository statistics.
.PP
Displays information about the test repository including total runs, latest
run ID, tests in latest run, failures in latest run, and total tests
executed across all runs.
.SS "slowest"
Show the slowest tests from the last run.
.PP
Displays test execution times sorted from slowest to fastest, with timing
information and percentage of total time.
.TP
\fB\-n\fR, \fB\-\-count\fR \fI\,N\/\fR
Number of tests to show (default: 10)
.TP
\fB\-\-all\fR
Show all tests
.SS "log"
Show logs for individual tests.
.PP
Displays logs and details for specific tests from a test run. Supports
glob\-style wildcard patterns for matching test IDs.
.TP
\fB\-r\fR, \fB\-\-run\fR \fI\,RUN_ID\/\fR
Run ID to show logs from (defaults to latest)
.TP
\fI\,TESTPATTERN\/\fR ...
Test ID patterns to match (glob\-style wildcards). If no patterns are
provided, shows all tests.
.SS "list\-tests"
List all available tests.
.PP
Queries the test command to discover all available tests in the test suite.
Requires a configuration file with a test_list_option or \-\-list flag.
.SS "analyze\-isolation"
Analyze test isolation issues using bisection.
.PP
Identifies test interactions by bisecting the test suite to find which tests
affect the outcome of a target test.
.TP
\fI\,TEST\/\fR
The test to analyze for isolation issues (required)
.PP
The command runs the target test in isolation, then runs all tests together,
and uses binary bisection to find and minimize the set of tests that
interact with the target test.
.SS "completions"
Generate shell completions.
.TP
\fI\,SHELL\/\fR
Shell to generate completions for (bash, zsh, fish, etc.)
.SS "upgrade"
Upgrade a .testrepository/ to .inquest/ format.
.PP
Migrates all test run data, failing tests, and timing information from the
legacy .testrepository/ format to the new .inquest/ SQLite\-based format.
Only available when compiled with the
.B testr
feature (enabled by default).
.SS "quickstart"
Show quickstart documentation.
.SS "help"
Show help information for commands.
.TP
\fI\,COMMAND\/\fR
Optional command name to show detailed help for
.SH CONFIGURATION
Configuration is read from
.B inquest.toml
in the repository root. Legacy
.B .testr.conf
(INI format) is also supported.
.PP
Key configuration options:
.TP
.B test_command
The command to run tests. Supports
.B $LISTOPT
and
.B $IDOPTION
placeholders.
.TP
.B test_id_option
Option to pass test IDs to the test command (e.g., \fB\-\-load\-list $IDFILE\fR)
.TP
.B test_list_option
Option to list available tests (e.g., \fB\-\-list\fR)
.SH FILES
.TP
.B .inquest/
Directory containing the test repository database and metadata
.TP
.B inquest.toml
Configuration file for the test runner
.TP
.B .testrepository/
Legacy test repository directory (can be upgraded with \fBinq upgrade\fR)
.SH EXAMPLES
Initialize and run tests:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
inq auto
inq run
.fi
.RE
.PP
Run only failing tests in parallel:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
inq run \-\-failing \-j4
.fi
.RE
.PP
Show the 5 slowest tests:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
inq slowest \-n 5
.fi
.RE
.PP
Load test results from a subunit stream:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
python \-m subunit.run discover | inq load
.fi
.RE
.PP
View logs for tests matching a pattern:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
inq log 'test_auth*'
.fi
.RE
.PP
Analyze test isolation for a specific test:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
inq analyze\-isolation mypackage.tests.test_foo.TestFoo.test_bar
.fi
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success (or no failing tests for test\-related commands)
.TP
.B 1
Failure (test failures detected or command error)
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR subunit (1),
.BR pytest (1),
.BR cargo\-test (1)
